{"INSNARE":[{"def":"To catch in a snare; to entrap; to take by artificial means.","pos":""},{"def":"To take by wiles, stratagem, or deceit; to involve in difficulties or perplexities; to seduce by artifice; to inveigle; to allure; to entangle.","pos":""}],"INSNARER":[{"def":"One who insnares.","pos":""}],"INSNARL":[{"def":"To make into a snarl or knot; to entangle; to snarl.","pos":""}]}